  "text": "End-to-end models such as Listen, Attend & Spell (LAS) [CITATION_1] or the Recurrent Neural Network Transducer (RNN-T) [CITATION_2] are sequence models that directly define P (W |X), the posterior probability of the word or subword sequence W given an audio frame sequence X, with no chaining of sub-module probabilities. State-of-the-art, or near state-of-the-art results have been reported for these models on challenging tasks [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
